  "text": "Bonferonni-corrected statistical threshold to account for multiple comparisons (5 regions) is p = 0.01. may contribute to the sensitivity of the BOLD measure. However, this increase in SNR by increasing the number of events may not be necessary [CITATION_1] . By contrast, a block design with a blue and yellow flashing checkerboard stimulus, which would increase the extent of activation has been used [CITATION_2] . This difference in stimulus and presentation appears to indicate that replicating the exact task is not a requirement in detecting a relationship between GABA concentration and BOLD activation. The spatial blurring in previous studies was not drastically different from that used in the current study (previous studies used a 5 or 8 mm FWHM kernel, compared to the 6 mm kernel applied here), therefore changes in SNR due to spatial blurring are unlikely to explain differing results.",
